by Scott Etkin   |   March 10, 2014 6:56 pm   |   0 Comments Former NSA contractor and whistleblower Edward Snowden spoke at SXSW via videoconference on Monday.Former NSA contractor Edward Snowden, noted for leaking details of data-collection programs of the U.S. National Security Agency and agencies of the United Kingdom, Australia, Canada, and New Zealand – countries of the Five Eyes alliance – to The Guardian and The Washington Post, spoke publicly on Monday by videoconference at the South by Southwest Music Conference and Festival in Austin, Texas.Snowden discussed why he chose to address the tech community rather than policymakers, encryption and the efforts to undermine it, and the need for developers to create more secure networks.Related StoriesCloud Analytics Expert: Adopt Data Security When You Begin a Project.
